Make creation more clear The previous creation implementation left a lot of gray area of how the messages were to be created. This adds fields to the create messages that make it clear what is required to properly form a Data Object or Bundle.

Add more comments, change id search to alias Being able to GET by ID and list using aliases seems like a more natural functionality. This makes one have to write a simple script to get all of the version of a document, but that seems like a rare edge case.
Remove id from creation During creation one should not specify the ID as it will be assigned by the DOS instance. To control the naming scheme aliases should be used.

Remove checksum URL All of the functionality of get-by-checksum is possible using a single endpoint. Simplifies the offering.

Normalize id usage, add update messages. Changes id names to be more descriptive. Adds message types for data bundle.

Rearrange entries, change package name The variable names weren\'t normalized to each other which was confusing. This rearranges the file to be more readable, adds message types where needed, and begins a refactor to replace the context-less \'id\' with .
Remove extraneous methods The features underlying these methods are made possible by the data object message itself. Services that simplify the response can use underlying API methods.
Add GetDataObject It seems we lacked a basic get by id functionality. Renamed the variable name to data_object_id to be more descriptive which led to other minor changes.

Move remaining service messages to service.proto
Remove the urls message from a bundle The URL for a bundle is really just the list of URLs for the underlying data objects.
Commit swagger in proper place We should try to automate away this part as part of the build, testing, or release. Checking in swagger JSON is not terribly helpful.
Remove has_keys search Arbitrarily searching amongst fields is difficult to align across implementations. To get to a minimum set I propose removing the ability to search on metadata.

Remove links data structure To access files in multiple cloud stores we expect them to be addressed by content and alias. However, the secondary layer of metadata discovery should be handled elsewhere to simplify implementations.

Remove provenance field For the sake of implementation simplicity I suggest to remove any optional fields that might be fulfilled using other means to avoid feature creep as we find the minimum set of functional features. The same file may have different provenance to get into different storage clouds, and the DOS is not a record of pipeline operations just a place to gather and store their results.

Remove metadata fields Metadata fields can be indexed using other means. DOS is meant to provide a file layer that can provide multicloud storage. These metadata can be provided in the info and indexed appropriately. If a typed tag bag is desired we might consider something more extensible like the attributes message in ga4gh-schemas.

Revision following extended discussions between Richard, Adam, Benedict, David H and Heng. The graph model now has Sequences and Joins, which join two arbitrary oriented positions (sometimes known as sides) in sequences. We also remove the NO_STRAND option in the Strand enum - this should be done by setting the variable to null.

Change specification search of name search from a substring match to exact name match.  Substring matching on searches is of limit value and is dangrous, potentially producing inconsistent, difficult to predict results.  There was no way to escape the substring matching behavior to get exact matches.  If pattern searches are required, a separate parameter should be added that supports regular expressions.

Improvements to the variants API When no callsetIds have been requested avoid entering the call object creation loop. Variant sets keep an index of the position of callsetIds to avoid iterating through the list of callsets. Removed hacks before pysam had implemented phased calls. pysam will say a single genotype is a phased call, which disagrees with pyvcf. This test has been commented out. Improve assembly of call object leading to fewer lookups. Remove now defunct tests Changed call to convertVariant in VA code to avoid callSetIds=None path.

summary of post-PR changes: - revert back to nd4j 0.5.0 (for the time being, it is the most memory efficient release) - made ComputableGraphStructure serializable (not necessary -- just for better semantics) - added a method to ICG to "nullify" a cached value (used for freeing up memory) - removed the NEGLECT_ZERO_COPY_NUMBER_STATE back in calculating log copy ratio posteriors; inclusion of finite mapping error correction to copy ratios obviates this - added IntegerCopyNumberReferenceStateFactory; essentially, a bi-fuction that takes a target and sex genotypes and gives the reference copy number state - improved Nd4jIOUtils; we can now read/write tensors to tab-separated files - the reported log likelihood now includes are normalization factors and the contribution from the HMM chain - CoverageModelCopyRatioEmissionProbabilityCalculator takes into account mapping error in the laplace approximation as well (this still has to be replaced with the "proper" laplace approximation) - ARD for bias covariates; this affects many classes (mainly CoverageModelEMWorkspace and CoverageModelEMComputeBlock) - PCA initialization of bias covariates - removed unnecessary setters in CoverageModelEMParams; added a validation method - some code cleanup and refactoring in CoverageModelEMWorkspace and CoverageModelEMComputeBlock (mostly relating to posterior initialization) - new methods in CoverageModelEMWorkspaceMathUtils for calculating eigensystems, log det, etc - added methods to clear caches values from variable transition probability caches - we no longer collect fbResults to the master node as they are too large to fit in a single machine's memory with 3+ copy number states. Instead, HiddenMarkovModelSegmentProcessor directly gives viterbi results (calculations are done on worker nodes). - added a method to ForwardBackwardAlgorithm to calculate the log data likelihood excluding emission lines (only the chain); this is useful in reporting the correct log likelihood in variational Bayes problems after updating some posteriors that affect emission probability, though, still using the old copy ratio posteriors - improved concordance statistics report in CoverageModellerGermlineSparkToggleIntegrationTest - extra unit tests for Nd4j-related methods - updated unit test resources

The main commit (coverage model). The commit may still be broken into the following modules: - computable graph related classes (coveragemodel/cachemanager) - math routines (coveragemodel/linalg, coveragemodel/math, coveragemodel/nd4jutils) - the EM algorithm (coveragemodel/*.java) - integer copy number transition prior (exome/germlinehmm/IntegerCopyNumber*) - unit and integration tests

Modifications of existing classes: - refactoring of some XHMM-related classes - small feature additions to target coverage sex genotyper - small feature additions to read count collection, utils, and unit tests - a fork of the existing HMM processor classes for segmentation-only (no VCF creation)

Major changes to the command line parsing system -using jopt-simple to do the actual parsing -supports short (-h) and long (--help) styles -supports boolean flags with or without an argument -options are now case sensitive -argument collections can be specified with @ArgumentCollection -Option(fullname) is now respected if specified, if it isn't it defaults to use the field name -several Option values are no longer used, overrideable -NestedOptions removed -> replaced by ArgumentCollection -Arguments must now be uniquely specified (no arguments targetting multiple fields any more) -Collection defaults are now replaced rather than appended too

the disk backed queue should set "canAdd" to false whenever we have spilled to disk and have started removing records from RAM, or whenever we start removing records from disk.  The pathology was that we would let callers add if there was any room in ram, regardless if we had spilled records to disk, thus causing records to become out of order. If the entire queue is empty, we set canAdd to true again.  Added test to make sure an exception is thrown if we add when we should not.

Issue #196 - fixes a bug which causes an overflow in the CIGAR when a BAM file is parsed that contains a read that spans a very large intron. The bug is caused by the use of an arithmetic (>>) rather than a logical (>>>) right shift operator in BinaryCigarCodec.binaryCigarToCigarElement(). This fix substitutes the logical for the arithmetic operator, and implements a test which reads the sample BAM file (containing a single record) that exposed the bug and compares the indexing bin field with the computed indexing bin field. If the two fields are different, an error is thrown.

Speed up adapter-finding code, which is used in IlluminaBasecallsToSam, IlluminaBasecallsToFastq, and MarkIlluminaAdapters.  By default, adapter sequences will be truncated at 30 characters, and any adapter pairs that become duplicates as a result are folded together.  After 100 adapters have been identified in reads, the list of adapter candidates is pruned down to the one adapter pair that was most frequent among the 100 reads with adapter sequence found.  In small tests, this has reduced IlluminaBasecallsToSam execution time by about 40%.  Moreover, since in most cases an Illumina lane uses only one adapter pair, pruning the list down to one pair reduces the chance that a read will be incorrectly marked with an adapter pair that was not used in the lane.  Note that for IlluminaBasecallsToSam and IlluminaBasecallsToFastq, there is no control over the configuration of this functionality.  However, MarkIlluminaAdapters has new command-line options that control all of the above behavior.

Added new SAMFileReader.query method that enables querying of multiple intervals in a single invocation.  In many cases this will be much more efficient than querying each interval separately, because due to the limitations of BAM index a query can result in many records read from the file that do not satisfy the query parameters.  In multiple query invocations, the same regions of the file may be read more than once, whereas with the new method each candidate region of the file will be read only once.

Configure Picard-public so that (1) IntelliJ and ant compile to different places and (2) IntelliJ ignores all of the ant compile locations (so that, for example, it does see all the ant .class files and think they are part of the source). Added funcitonality to .bcl-reading command line programs to better handle qualities less than 2 via BclQualityEvaluationStrategy.  When an application encounters such a quality score, it used to throw an exception immediately; now, it will convert write a quality 1 to the underlying file (bam, fastq, etc.), and at the end of reading the BCLs, it may or may not throw an exception depending on the strictness of the BclQualityEvaluationStrategy.  It will always log a warning message if a quality is encountered, regardless of whether or not an exception is thrown.

Better message when SortingCollection fills up TMP_DIR.

Add additional clean-up: set MAPQ to 0 if a read is unmapped.
Set SortingCollection.destructiveIteration true by default, in order to enable earlier GC of no-longer-needed SAMRecords.
Significant code refactoring in IlluminaBasecallsToSam; overhaulded threading model to improve CPU utilization; added test for Tile comparator
Synchronized record() method to make class thread-safe

Added single-jar packaging target tasks.  Consolidated package-commands task.

Augmented plots for GC Bias Metrics, Mean Quality by Cycle, Quality Score Distribution, and RNA Sequence Coverage.  Specifically, if the plot was generated from a read group .bam, the title of the plot includes the read group's library.

added method to make a read unmapped and a method to check whether any cigar element consumes both read and reference bases to SAMUtils; used these methods in AbstractAlignment merger to catch reads with cigar strings that don't consume any read or reference bases (e.g. all soft-clipped) and make them unmapped
Handle case where an alignment record has no cigar elements that consume both the read and the reference (e.g. the read is all soft-clipped)
Add support for targetedPcrMetrics and collected common HsMetrics and TargetedPcrMetrics behavior into TargetMetricsCollector
Slightly improved elapsed time output in ProgressLogger.

Added a new "ProgressLogger" class that facilitates more useful and standard progress logging for any program that iterates through a stream of SAMRecords.  Adapted most command line programs to use it.
Add ability to set DT tag in new read group.
Fix NPE caused by broken copy ctor for PerUnitHsMetricCollector.
Clearer error message when paired reads but SECOND_END_FASTQ is not specified.
Fix unit test broken by last check-in.
Fixed naming issues that were failing the build
Abstract metric accumulation functionality into MultiLevelCollector and refactor all classes that use MultilevelMetrics
Switch SortingLongCollection from memory-mapped I/O to DataInput/OutputStream, in order to avoid problems due to JVM's delayed release of mapped memory.

Performance fix to EstimateLibraryComplexity.  Previously it would attempt to find duplicates within all groups of reads with a common prefix which would bog down if a technical sequence like adapter dimer dominated the library.  The fix is just to ignore groups that have > some large multiple of the expected average number of read pairs per group.  The default is 500 times over the mean.

Add option PRIMARY_ALIGNMENT_STRATEGY to MergeBamAlignment, which enables selection of the strategy for selecting the primary alignment for a read if there are multiple alignments marked as primary, or if none of the alignments for a read are marked as primary. In addition to the existing strategy, BestMapq, add a new strategy EarliestFragment which only works for fragments, and selects the alignment that maps the earliest base in a read.
Add support for adding arbitrary header tags to read groups via IlluminaBasecallsToSam.java
Fixed bug when dealing with dual barcodes.  IlluminaBasecallsToSam now expects NO dashes(-) in matchedBarcode
Close output files before throwing exception due to unpaired mates.
Allow writing a BAM file to a stream that is not associated with a File.
Added more descriptive error message for the case of fewer bases available in Qseqs compared to cycles found in the read structure of a run
Miscellaneous util changes and ExtractIlluminaBarcodes bug fix for handling multiple barcodes
Fix bug in which one overload of adapterTrimIlluminaPairedReads was ignoring minMatchBases and maxErrorRate arguments and using default values.
Small changes to ExtractIlluminaBarcodes to allow the use of quality scores to perform more stringent barcode calling.
Added a convenience ReadDescriptor accessor to ReadStructure.Substructure
Added a synchronized block around series of writes to System.out so that messages won't get interleaved when multiple threads log simultaneously.
Fix ArrayOutOfBounds exceptions when ReadStructure has a skip before its last ReadDescriptor
Make CloseableIterators on BAM files idempotent on close().
Added a newTempFile() method that defaults the amount of space needed free on the tmp filesystem.
Speed up SamFileHeaderMerger in cases where we have many collisions
Add standard options -h, -H, --version to HTML doc. Clean up IntelliJ warnings.
Make SamToFastq work if there are no read groups in the input.
Fix multithreading bug happening in IlluminaBasecallsToSam
Erroneously removed a StringUtil method in previous commit
Made the random seed truly optional in DownsampleSam.
Initialize ADAPTERS_TO_CHECK to a mutable array so it can be changed on the command line.
Improve error message about absence of SO:coordinate in header.

Pass filename through to BAMRecordCodec to improve error messages.

Major refactoring of ClippingUtil underlying IlluminaBasecallsToSam.  All existing adapterTrim... methods are deprecated and no longer return any warning strings.  ClippingUtliity.AdapterPair has been removed and now their is an AdapterPair interface (in the util package) that is implemented by IlluminaAdapterPair.  In IlluminaBasecallsToSam the MARK_ADAPTER paramter has been removed and replaced with ADAPTERS_TO_CHECK, which is a list of IlluminaAdapterPairs.  If any adapter pairs are provided, adapter marking is done.  New adapter pairs have been added and the defaults in use have changed.
Just a little tidying in the metrics doclet.
Removed an import that was automatically added by accident.
Fix for bug whereby the FastqWriters were being close()'d multiple times if not outputting per read-group and multiple read groups were present in the input sam/bam file.
IlluminaDataProvider no longer parses position files to get tile/lane information.  It get's this from any available parser (and therefore avoids unnecessary parsing of position files).
IlluminaDataProvider and dependent classes (IlluminaBasecallsToSam, ExtractIlluminaBarcodes) will no longer load/copy files and data for skipped cycles
Added a set of "dual indexed" adapters.
Fix for problem where PF_ALIGNED_BASES AND PF_MISMATCH_RATE were being calculated on all aligned bases, not just PF.
Adding documentation links *  CommandLinePrograms now print web documentation link in Usage *  The FAQ link is printed when exceptions are thrown
change delimitor for multiple-barcode concatenation from slash to hyphen
modified MeanQualityByCycle so that it does not try to generate an R plot if there is no data in the metrics file.

Two changes: 1) Implemented a tiny custom sublcass of GZIPOutputStream so that the compression level could be adjusted from the default compression level (5), and made it to that IoUtil.openFileForWriting() and friends that vector to our GZIP writing code override the default using Defaults.COMPRESSION_LEVEL which is settable via system property.

IlluminaDataProvider now supports (and prefers) BCLs and other binary data types over QSeqs.  If BCLs,Pos,Locs,Clocs, or filter files are present then IlluminaDataProvider will use these file formats.  However, if one type of data requested requires the use of QSeqs then QSeqs will be used for all data provided (to avoid unecessarily parsing extra files).  This change includes other misc. refactorings within the Illumina package.
Updated DownsampleBam to ignore all non-primary alignments so that pairs don't get mishandled.

Minor change to allow direct setting of the bait set name via a command line parameter instead of inferring it from the filename. Inference is still used if explicit name isn't passed.

Don't use regex to truncate sequence name at first whitespace, to improve speed.

Reworking of the AsyncSAMFileWriter to move most code into a superclass and reuse it to create AsyncFastqWriter. NOTE: FastqWriter has been converted to an interface and must now be constructed via the new FastqWriterFactory.

Large refactoring of IlluminaDataProvider and related code.  Important things: The public interface of the Illumina package has become much smaller but nearly everything that has been removed is provided by IlluminaDataProvider.  There is a new IlluminaDataType (Position) which most users will likely want to include when using IlluminaDataProvider, this data of this type used to be added automatically when a user chose any type that required QSeqs.  Previously deprecated options have been removed from IlluminaDataProviderFactory as well as one or two that are no longer used.  ClusterData (the product of an IlluminaDataProvider) now has an array of ReadData rather than one,two,or three reads.  There will be one more round of possibly disruptive updates to the IlluminaDataProvider code.  Currently IlluminaDataProvider determines an IlluminaRunConfiguration from available QSeq files, in future updates the user will have to provide this information.

Modifications to support an ordered list of temp directories in Picard programs.  Programs will generally use the list in order unti there is insufficient free space in a directory to be sure of completely writing a file there. Added a method to get the column names back.
added flag for skipping blank lines in input files (now the default behavior)
Add IGNORE_SEQUENCE option to CollectRnaSeqMetrics to enable specification of one or more sequences that should not be counted in most of the RNA seq metrics.
Added tab separator for reading metrics files instead of default whitespace separator, to better handle data that includes sample names which may have spaced in them.

Add support for array tag values (type B) for signed and unsigned byte, short, int; and for float.  Note that previously byte arrays were stores as hex ascii string (type H).  Type H will still be read, but no longer written.  The only exception is that if a BAM record containing a tag of H type is read from a file, and none of the variable length part of the BAM record is changed, then if the BAM record is written to another file, the tag will still be H type.
change script so that spaces are tolerated in sample/library names, columns separated on tabs only
Add option to disable soft clipping if 3' end of read extends past 5' end of mate.
Fix downstream unit test break caused by CREATE_INDEX static data member being changed in unit test.
Unit test to confirm that unsorted input can produce properly sorted output.
Fix bug created 7/28 in which if input were unsorted, SORT_ORDER=coordinate was ignored.
Handle case in which EXPECTED_ORIENTATIONS is not set on the command line properly.
Added check that there's actually data in the histogram to plot before calling R.
Lazily initialize ByteArrayOutputStream so that it is not allocated if readLine is never called.
Improved version of readLine that fixes bugs and handles CRLF properly.
Added a plot of normalized position along transcript vs. normalized coverage to the RNA seq metrics.

Added a handful more metrics to RNA metrics: PF_BASES, PCT_USABLE_BASES and MEDIAN_5PRIME_TO_3PRIME_BIAS
Refactor previous change to make it less error prone (I hope).

Clarify that available() method may block.
Give getProgramRecord argument a clearer name.
Speed up Histogram.trimByWidth for large histograms.

Modified CollectAlignmentSummaryMetrics, CollectInsertSizeMetrics and CalculateHsMetrics to support collection of metrics at multiple levels: ALL_READS is the default and will caulate metrics based on all reads in the file; SAMPLE will caculate a separate metric for each sample in the file; LIBRARY will calculate metrics for each library and READ_GROUP will do the same for each read group.  Metrics can be caculated for multiple levels (e.g. SAMPLE and LIBRARY level can be calculated in one pass).  The output files contain three new columns: SAMPLE, LIBRARY, and READ_GROUP.  If all three are blank, the metric applies to all reads in the file.  If only SAMPLE is non-blank, then the metrics applies to the sample listed.  If only SAMPLE and LIBRARY are non-blank, then the metric applies to the LIBRARY listed.  If all three are filed in, then the metric applies to the READ_GROUP listed./

Improve error message when sequence dictionary is not present.

Add new overload of assertSequenceDictionariesEqual that reports filenames.

Don't throw an exception if a read is unmapped.

Added code for two new features: 1) the addition of HS AT and GC dropout metrics to measure GC bias in a way similar to whole genome data, but just for the target regions. 2) the addition of a PER_TARGET_COVERAGE option which allows the output of detailed per-target metrics for ad-hoc analysis.

Include Linux Snappy DLL in executable jars.
Fixed a bug in a test caused by a bugfix in Histogram.getMedian()!
More robust implementation of getMedian that does the right thing if there are an even number of things in the histogram.

Changed CollectInsertSizeMetrics to use a more sensible approach to trimming the distribution of insert sizes before calculating the mean and sd, and for sizing the plot.  The new method is simply to trim the distribution to [0..(median + 10median_absolute_deviation)].  This works well when the distribution is mostly normal (approximating mean+6.7sd), and is much more robust to bimodality and other strange distributions.
Added methods for calculating:  1) The geometric mean  2) The median absolute deviation  3) Estimating the SD of a quasi-normal distribution via the median absolute deviation
Added a PF_INDEL_RATE to collect alignment summary metrics that calculates total number of short insertions/deletions seen in reads / total aligned pf bases.
Add option SORTING_COLLECTION_SIZE_RATIO to deal with out-of-memory issues.
Fixed an index out of bounds error in passesQualityCheck.
Cleaner version of jar with some extraneous junk removed.
Add Snappy for optional compression of temp files written by SortingCollection.

Added a new tool called IntervalListTools that can be used to sort, merge, unique, pad and report on what's in an interval list.

Fixes bug in BasicInputParser where getCurrentLine and getCurrentLineNumber methods return information about  the *next* line rather than the current one.

Add public for unit test use.
Add usage message. Eliminate STRIP_LEADING_CHR command-line option.
Eliminate sequence dictionary command-line argument. Make rRNA interval list command-line argument optional.
Fixed bug in TabbedTextFileParser and added test to verify.
Fix to correctly rename bam index file along without bam output when creating index.
Printing out offending line when parser fails
Move RnaSeqMetrics to the correct package.
Clean up naming of RNA-seq programs and metrics.

Fix for a bug in calculating the HS_PENALTY_nnX numbers that was triggered if the input sequence data provided massively more coverage than needed to cover 80% of targets at nX.  In cases where the coverage was below, at or modestly above target coverage levels this wasn't a problem.
added ability to retrieve full (non-split) line from Row in TabbedTextFileWithHeaderParser
Revert change to support FTP URLs because they aren't seekable.
Allow FTP as well as HTTP URL connection (patch courtesy of Lance Frohman).
Changes to ensure that cleanup() is called on all instances of SortingCollection and SortingLongCollection after use, to ensure that temporary files are cleaned up ASAP.
Added an output of the elapsed time when a program ends.
Do not copy non-primary alignments into reverted SAM.
Fixed PF_HQ_ERROR_RATE, overflow error due to previous simplification of CollectAlignmentSummaryMetrics.java
Remove getAlignmentAtPosition until it's fixed as getReferencePositionAtReadPosition

Refactored AbstractTextFileParser, TabbedTextFileParser, and BasicTextFileParser as AbstractInputParser, TabbedInputParser, and BasicInputParser.  All now have additional constructors that take InputStreams, and the old constructors that take Files are still there.  Except for the name change, they should continue to work the same as before.
Clean up bad imports, fix IntelliJ warnings.
Count bases that match ribosomal sequence. Count alignments with correct and incorrect strand for strand-specific library prep.
Ignore non-primary alignments when gathering metrics.
Move location of HTTP-accessed BAM from SourceForge web to Broad web, because SF doesn't serve this file reliably (perhaps because BAM is GZIP-encoded?)
Simplified CollectAlignmentSummaryMetrics.java and added PF_ALIGNED_BASES, and PF_MISMATCH_RATE to AlignedSummaryMetrics, CollectAlignmentSummaryMetrics, and the test
changes to avoid NPE when calling equals() method on SAMRecord
Do not consider non-primary alignments as potential duplicates.
Put back deprecated option GENERATE_SECONDARY_BASECALLING in IlluminaBasecallsToSam.  It will be removed in a future update.
Added IlluminaBasecallsToSam, ExtractIlluminaBarcodes, and supporting classes, utilities, and tests
Fix bug in SeekableFileStream.  read() should return -1 if nothing could be read due to EOF.  Fix courtesy of Matt Mead.
Enable MergeBamAlignment to handle multiple alignments for the same read.
Undid last accidentally committed changes allowing N to match in basesEqual
Add option to BAM index reading code to disable memory mapping of index file.
Changes to centralize the size of buffers use in various buffering file read/writing classes and default them to 128kb.
Make SortingCollection in-memory iteration destructive by default in order to reduce memory footprint.
Modified to throw the original error, even if there is an exception when writing out the final log lines
Last commit of SortingCollection introduced a call to a Java 1.6 API.  This commit fixes that :)
Some very minor changes to remove a System.err.println and make the copy constructor a little cleaner.

1) Added a little progress logging to SortSam 2) Changed SortingCollection to use a TreeSet in place of a PriorityQueue; this results in a speed up on the order of ~20% for the merging phase of SortingCollection when there are large numbers of temp files in use.
Eliminate work-around for SourceForge HTTP problem http://sourceforge.net/apps/trac/sourceforge/ticket/18367, since it no longer seems to be a problem.

Restor value of SAMFileReader.defaultValidationStringency in various places where it is changed, so that methods that are typically main programs can be called in the context of some other program, and don't mess up the original validation stringency.
Augment comparator to test not-primary flag and hit-index (HI) tag value, if present. Encapsulate read name comparator in case it gets changed.
Code review corrections.  Added ReservedTagConstant OC for Original Cigar
Removed recently introduced overload of makeReferenceFromAlignment and its test
Handle packaging changes for inner classes of metrics files
Added a warning message if a sequence doesn't have any bases while normalizing.
changed histogram holder from HashMap to EnumMap so that metrics file will output in a predictable order
When a read has negative strand flag set, reverse-complement it regardless of whether it is mapped or not, and clear the flag.
Added method to get size of directory tree, and also added a boolean return code to deleteDirectoryTree
PIC-483 Flush output stream so that message that error list has been truncated is emitted.
Added a method to get the size, in bytes, of a file or directory tree.
PIC-482 -- Make sure BAM index is created when indexing on the fly, even when the output BAM does not contain any reads.
Reverse complement all reads with the negativeStrandFlag set, even if they are unmapped

Significant refactoring of MergeBamAlignment.  AbstractAlignmentMerger and SamAlignmentMerger have been modified to use the expected orientations of read pairs rather than a boolean for whether the library is a jumping library.  They have new constructors and code that uses these directly will have to be modified to use them.  MergeBamAlignment has retained JUMP_SIZE for backwards compatiblity, but it has been deprecated and uses should switch to providing EXPECTED_ORIENTATIONS.
Eliminate test that relied on large BAM stored on SF.
Moved AddOrReplaceReadGroups from test to java folder
Modified AbstractAlignmentMerger and SamAlignment merger to handle (a) multiple files of alignments and (b) separate alignments of both ends of a paired read
Added a new utility to add or replace the (possibly empty) set of read groups in an existing SAM or BAM file, contributed by Mark DePristo.

Added a new utility called ReorderSam (contributed by Mark DePristo) which is designed to take a SAM/BAM file and switch out the sequence dictionary for one in a different order, and then re-order the INPUT file to produce a coordinate sorted OUTPUT file with respect to the new sequence dictionary.
Adding functionality to SamToFastq to optionally trim read 1 or read 2 and to optionally write a maximum number of bases (post-trimming) to the fastq file.
Converted to use arrays internally to reduce runtime by 30-40%.
Add SeekableHTTPStream ctor that takes a Proxy object.
SamToFastq was NPEing if @RG.PU did not exist.  I have modified it to fall back to using @RG.ID if @RG.PU is null and we are doing output per read group.
Hack to fix strange problem with reading BAM via HTTP from SourceForge.
Fixed to cope with the situation when there are no valid bases in an input sam/bam file.
Couple of minor fixes to yesterday's changes.

Adds a .equals method to MetricBase that compares the values for all public fields in the class; modifies MetricFile to have separate comparison methods for header, metrics, and histogram and to call all three of them in the .equals method.  FormatUtil now handles Bytes.
Faster implementation of MeanQualityByCycle that cuts off about 2/3 of the runtime.
Made sure that the list of programs to run is unique.
Eliminate requirement that fields annotated with @Option and @Usage be public.
Clean up temp files in unit test.
In CollectGcBiasMetrics, when counting errors in GC window, add # of inserted bases and # of deleted bases to # of mismatched bases.
Fixed a bug whereby windows from a reference sequence were ignored if the reference sequence had no reads aligned to it.
Add ability to set PI, DS, DT tags in read group in FastqToSam.
Added an option to set the sequencing center.
Nothing to release, so rolling back version # increment.
Moved across source folders to the test folder.
Change name of release_notes.txt to README.txt to accomodate Sourceforge.
Suppress validation for zero-length read bases if SAMRecord is not primary.
Fix to not check sequence dictionary equality when the input file has no seuqence dictionary.
First version of a multi-metrics tool.  Still fairly primitive.
More efficient implementation of Historam.getStandardDeviation() and unit tests for the same.
Unit test for CollectAlignmentSummaryMetrics when read length 0
Reads shorter than ADAPTER_MATCH_LENGTH are not considered adapters. Fixes ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException from samtools-dev when 0-length read
Change behavior of RevertSam so that if REMOVE_DUPLICATE_INFORMATION=false, then the output can have records with the duplicate flag set despite being unaligned.
The SAM Header is now parsed for libaries in order to try to pre-populate the metrics objects because otherwise there would be no duplication metrics objects for a library if no reads were found
If no reads are found than an empty unpaired category metric is output
MetricsFile.read will not throw an exception if the EOF is reached in before any metrics are read.  Instead an empty metrics file object is returned
Changes to IntervalList to ensure that only intervals defined against valid sequences can be loaded from file.
When not using index, halt iteration as soon as a read is seen that is after the last interval requested.
Undid last commit - awaiting unit tests
Validate that cigar's readLength matches record's readLenth
Fixed the check that the BamIndexFile lastModifiedDate >= BamFile.lastModifiedDate
Optimized getMetaData to avoid query PIC-465
Fixed most of the problems running unit tests on windows

Non-standard header tag values are no longer typed.  They are all stored as strings.  Any existing files that have a non-standard header tag value with a value type encoded in it will need to be repaired.  These header tags will parse, but may not yield the expected results.
Soft-clip CIGAR operator inside of hard-clip operator is now considered valid.
When merging the input files, if they are all sorted then use that to produce a sorted input iterator.
Improve interface to bam index metaData - public getMetaData in AbstractBamFileIndex.
Support bgzipped SAM files in SAMFileReader.
Changes needed by 454 - accidentally left off last commit
Changes needed by 454 - accidentally left off last commit
Provide more informative error message when countMismatches has an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException.
Added a new tool to extract subsequences from a fasta file.
Fix HTML help generation for TMP_DIR so it has a more generic default value.
Added validation that bait and target files are the same reference as the reads
Emit warning if MD5 or BAM index creation is requested, but can't be done because output BAM is not a regular file.
Fix auto-MD5 generation, which wasn't working because of check that output file already exists rather than that it is a normal path.
CollectAlignmentSummaryMetricsTest now tests for a case with no reference sequence provided.
CollectAlignmentSummaryMetrics no longer fails if there is no reference sequence provided.
Segregated tests to handle printing html usage with and without standard options.

CommandLinePrograms no longer display common options unless -H or --stdhelp is used or there was an error with a standard option.  Modified option and the CreateHTML source files to add a common attribute to identify options as common.

Tests changed to reflect FastqToSam no longer fails on read if trailing /1 or /2 is missing IF the read names are identical AND don't end in /1 or /2.  Also changed test execution process to include argument parsing in CommandLineProgram.
FastqToSam no longer fails on read if trailing /1 or /2 is missing IF the read names are identical AND don't end in /1 or /2
Added test data for SamToFastqTest to test OUTPUT_PER_RG option.
Modified test to handle new OUTPUT_PER_RG and added new test files .

SamToFastq may now output fastq files per read group if OUTPUT_PER_RG (OPRG) is specified.  If OUTPUT_DIR is specified with OUTPUT_PER_RG then a file (two if paired end) will be output in OUTPUT_DIR per read group named after the platform unit for the read group.
Added simple method to lowercase a byte.
Flush output files before checking for unpaired mates.
When trying to find a sequence dictionary corresponding to a reference fasta, try filename.dict if basename.dict isn't found.  Patch from Nils Homer.
Added a method to read an entire InputStream and create a String.
When trying to find a sequence dictionary corresponding to a reference fasta, try filename.dict if basename.dict isn't found.  Patch from Nils Homer.
PIC-447 Store PairEndInfo in file-based data structure so it runs in fixed amount of RAM.  Added check for read marked as paired for which a mate is not found.
Fix so that it can handle storing a PairInfo in which the mate reference index is -1.
Modified so we don't try to calculate UQ tag if QUAL is set to *

PIC-188 Enable MarkDuplicates to work in a reasonable amount of RAM even for a reference with many sequences, by using an LRU cache for open file handles in order to avoid exceeding maximum number of open file handles.  MAX_SEQUENCES_FOR_DISK_READ_ENDS_MAP option is obsolete.  MAX_FILE_HANDLES_FOR_READ_ENDS_MAP controls the size of the LRU cache.
Change validation on to check for end < start-1 (instead of end < start) since end = start-1 is used to represent 0-length intervals
Throw FileNotFoundException in IndexedFastaSequenceFile ctor if index is not found.
Don't attempt to validate the index of a Sam file

Added a check that the program record id handed in or present in the aligned BAM file is not already in use in the unmapped BAM

Fix ArrayBoundException in BamIndexStats when no alignments

new utility method to initialize CLP default collection with modifiable lists
Minor edit to how bait set name is derived from the bait intervals file.

Fixed to no longer throw an exception if there is insufficient data to plot.  Also added an optimization to stop when it reaches the unmapped reads at the end of the file.

Fix array bound check that was preventing linear index optimization
Fix for bug where samRecord2.getSecondOfPairFlag() was being called without checking that samRecord2 is paired.

Fix bugs and improved optimization of indexed queries.
Fix for infinite loop in SAMRecord.clone()

In BlockCompressedOutputStream, when compressed block is too big, downshift to NO_COMPRESSION mode instead of pushing some input into the next block.  Reduce max uncompressed bytes per GZIP block so that in NO_COMPRESSION mode these will always fit in the GZIP block.

Change to allow users to decide whether or not to compute and validate CRCs when decompressing BAMs and other block compressed GZIP data. Default is to not validate CRCs since it's an expensive operation.

Change to allow users to decide whether or not to compute and validate CRCs when decompressing BAMs and other block compressed GZIP data. Default is to not validate CRCs since it's an expensive operation.

Add ability to generate package command without generating HTML documentation.

Took a second look at the comments and changed some to improve clarity.
A bit of miscellaneous cleanup of the last checkin.
Cleanups and doc improvements requested by Alec.
Rename new method and a little more javadoc.
Renamed method for clairity and consistency
Modified and added a few methods to make them take ints instead of longs since we use ints everywhere.

Pushing changes from hanna_dev to hanna_full.

Push command-line usage up to sourceforge.
Fix default value for JAVA_HOME_1_5.  On our Linux Java installation, java.home refers to jre directory which doesn't contain javac.

Check that SAMFileReader passed to SamLocusIterator is coordinate sorted.

Add SAMFileReader ctor that takes a SeekableStream, so BAM files can be read from arbitrary sources like FTP or Aspera.
Made a few quality/fastq conversion methods public.

Change to try and reduce the number of totally identical sequence dictionaries kept in memory during a merge operation.

Changes to only store a copy of the full SAM header as a String if it is < 2MB in memory or if there are errors.  This should dramatically reduce the memory needed to merge files with large sequence dictionaries or other large headers.
Fix BlockCompressedInputStream.getFilePointer(), so that if current block is exhausted, it returns a pointer to the beginning of the next block.

When iterating over SAM text, don't parse a line until that line is requested by the caller, so that exceptions & warnings arrive at the appropriate time.  Previously it parsed line n+1 when the iterator was returning line n.
Set mIsBinary regardless of whether BAM is read from file or pipe.
Handle case in which BAM file to be read is a pipe rather than a regular file.

Test for whitespace trimming when loading fasta.

Minor change to make exception message a little more helpful.

PIC-179 All integer tags are now loaded from BAM as type Integer, regardless of whether they are stored at Byte, Char, Short or Integer.  They are now stored in BAM in the smallest encoding that will hold them.  Unsigned integer is not allowed, although with validation stringency set to lenient or silent an unsigned integer can be read from a BAM.  For SAM, a value greater than a signed 32-bit int cannot be read.
Simplified isSameSequence to compare only sequenceIndex, sequenceLength, and either MD5 or name.

After discovering that BufferedReader is faster than AsciiLineReader on Linux but slower on Mac, implemented class (AsciiLineReader) that detects OS and delegates to AsciiLineReaderImpl or BufferedLineReader as appropriate.  AsciiLineReaderImpl does byte=>char conversion itself rather than calling StringUtil.bytesToString() for better performance.
